gomodel:SYNGO_4954  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors developed an optical imaging assay in primary cell culture and first loaded the recycling synaptic vesicles with FM4-64 dye during 60 s of 20 Hz electrical stimulation (Gaffield and Betz, 2006; see Figure 7-figure supplement 1 for example images) and then monitored destaining with time-lapse fluorescence imaging during low frequency (0.2 Hz) stimulation in the absence of dye, followed by near complete destaining with a second 20 Hz train. The results indicate that destaining at 0.2Hz is significantly increased in synapses of different null mutants (SYP1,2 SYG1,3), most importantly between QKO and TKO + SYP1. Given other evidence in the same study (Fig 2-6), the data indicate that SYP1 is a negative regulator of exocytosis, and especially of fusogenicity, suggesting a role in the priming steps.\n\nProtein names; SYP1 = synaptophysin/SYP; SYP2 = synaptophysin-2 aka. synaptoporin/SYNPR; SYG1 = synaptogyrin-1/SYNGR1; SYG3 = synaptogyrin-3/SYNGR3.. Experimental description: Synaptophysin 1 antibody confirmed knockout of SYP (Fig 1, mouse line Jackson labs 008415)\nantibody: RRID:AB_2313839, Millipore mouse used at 1:2000" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4954" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

